<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10973] SolrJ: ContentType is not parsed properly in HttpSolrClient</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10973</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When multipart posting is used, the content type is passed to the constructor for InputStreamBody as a simple string:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;            parts.add(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; FormBodyPart(name,
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InputStreamBody(
                    content.getStream(),
                    contentType,
                    content.getName())));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is incorrect; HttpClient does not parse that contentType as anything other than a mime type and thus blows up when you pass in something like &quot;text/plain; charset=utf-8&quot;.  The correct code is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;            parts.add(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; FormBodyPart(name,
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InputStreamBody(
                    content.getStream(),
                    ContentType.parse(contentType),
                    content.getName())));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was discovered by a ManifoldCF user.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
